<body class="d-flex text-center text-white bg-dark">
    <div class="cover-container d-flex w-100 h-100 p-3 mx-auto flex-column">
        <header class="mb-auto">
            <div>
                <h3 class="float-md-start mb-0">MountainAir</h3>
                <nav class="nav nav-masthead justify-content-center float-md-end">
                    <div>
                        <a href="#" aria-current="page" class="nav-link active">Home</a>
                        <a href="/campgrounds" class="nav-link">Campgrounds</a>
                        <% if(!currentUser) { %>
                        <a href="/register" class="nav-link ">Register</a>
                        <a href="/login" class="nav-link">Login</a>
                        <% } else { %>
                        <a href="/logout" class="nav-link">Logout</a>
                        <% } %>
                    </div>
                </nav>
            </div>
        </header>
        <main class="px-3">
            <h1>MountainAir</h1>
            <p class="lead">
                This is MountainAir, <br>
                A project I've spent months developing the knowledge of for both the front-end and back-end stacks so that I can explore the current limits of my development skills <br>
                I made this because I have always liked camping and the oppertunities it provides for being out in nature and relaxing, I hope you like it too.
            </p>
            <a href="/campgrounds" class="btn btn-lg btn-secondary font-weight-bold text-white">
                Look At The Campgrounds
